[thinking] **Considering interface defaults**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm noticing a potential issue where applying the @Defaults annotation to an interface makes all unresolved methods default. If the target is missing but the method annotated with @Instance checks the parameters correctly—like validating regular non-array parameters and returning a boolean—it then sets a Boolean default. But what about simple default methods without @Defaults? I guess the solution would be to annotate the interface with @Defaults for those cases.
[thinking] 
