ass is included. However, it seems I might need to look into escaping issues. There’s something here that doesn’t quite add up, so I need to dig deeper.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Planning code adjustments**\\n\\nI'm looking at making a patch for the custom initial state machine, and I think I should rename the method too, maybe to something clearer? It's always good to keep things well-structured and intuitive. It might help others (or even future me) understand the code better. So, I’ll consider what name would best reflect its functionality. Let’s explore a few options for names and get this patch in place!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NIwZwNFPeSeZU8ULS0eNZ56d|fc_04065ac85cb3361e0169fc30cb699c819c82208032b414445f", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "tasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n    if ((JavaVersion.current().majorVersion as int) < 24) {\n        jvmArgs += [\"-Djava.security.manager=allow\"]\n    }\n}\n\ntasks.named(\"nativeTest\") {\n    if ((JavaVersion.current().majorVersion as int) < 24) {\n        runtimeArgs.add(\"-Djava.security.manager=allow\")\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "String permissiveSecurityManager = \"org_modelmapper.modelmapper.JavaDispatcherTest\\$PermissiveSecurityManager\"\n\ntasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n    if ((JavaVersion.current().majorVersion as int) < 24) {\n        jvmArgs += [\"-Djava.security.manager=${permissiveSecurityManager}\"]\n    }\n}\n\ntasks.named(\"nativeTest\") {\n    if ((JavaVersion.current().majorVersion as int) < 24) {\n        runtimeArgs.add(\"-Djava.security.manager=${permissiveSecurityManager}\")\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1120, "output": 2805, "cacheRead": 51200, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 55125, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timest